OL,6,FMr Justice Butcher said he had heard
OL,7,Fevidence of Barnard's good character,
OL,8,Fincluding being described as the "most
OL,9,Fcaring person on the staff" at the
OL,10,Fhome, and said it was unlikely she
OL,11,Fwould reoffend.
OL,13,FHe added: "I have no doubt as to your
OL,14,Fgenuine remorse.
OL,16,F"You have already suffered in respect
OL,17,Fof your mistake. You have been
OL,18,Fsuspended from your work and won't
OL,19,Freturn to that work."
